          <h2>Intro</h2>
          <p>This site was built as a prototype for a NodeJs backend and simple Bootstrap based SASS style scheme to mimic the existing functionality 
            of the TfL Online website at http://tfl.gov.uk. It was written in less than 50 hours of personal time and includes a GO language CMS page 
            processor that converts the Reddot generated razor (cshtml) pages into JSON objects that are then parsed using ejs templates. The site also
            demonstrates forms built along the gov.uk design guidelines (https://design-system.service.gov.uk/) to meet accessibility AA/AAA standards. 
            The site (when last updated) included about 3000 CMS pages which were 95% like for like.</p>
          <p>It does not include conversion of the main customised
            'functional' pages, such as Journey Planner, but does include some replicated design versions for key pages.</p>
          <p>It also includes ZERO custom javascript, and very little custom CSS/SASS. I was trying to prove that a siginficant protion of the 
            current codebase was unnecessary.</p>
